This paper deals with sequence classification tasks, which are commonly studied in the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses multi-task learning and semi-supervised learning techniques, which are common in machine learning (ML) research. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also evaluates its approach on a variety of tasks, including sentiment analysis, which involves analyzing text data. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also possible sub-categories.
